    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """The analysis of large volumes of data is used to support decision making and to build data intensive products and services, such as recommendation, prediction and diagnostic systems. The collection of skills required to perform these functions have been grouped under the term Data Science. This course develops the necessary skills around the Apache Spark platform, which is rapidly becoming the reference platform for mass data analysis. The course is structured around practical projects that include prediction, using automatic learning algorithms, collaborative filtering and pattern search. These exercises demonstrate in a practical way how to manipulate data sets through parallel processing with PySpark, Spark SQL, Spark Machine Learning Pipelines and SparkR.
In this course, you will:
Understand what high-volume data analysis is, its features, methods, and major platforms.
Understand the Apache Spark platform, its objectives, its components, and its programming model.
Write and debug Spark applications for mass data analysis.
Use Spark to develop data-intensive products and services, such as recommendation, prediction, and diagnostic systems, using parallel processing, Spark Machine Learning Pipelines, and Spark Streaming.
Use PySpark perform statistical analysis on large volumes of data"""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/jm.moya%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/jm.moya%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Ingeniería de Grandes Volúmenes de Datos"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/CE02> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE02" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Utilizar sistemas operativos, programas y herramientas de uso común en biología computacional, así como, manejar plataformas de cómputo de altas prestaciones, lenguajes de programación y análisis bioinformáticos/ Utilizing operative systems, software and tools commonly used in computational biology, and working with high throughput platforms, programing languages and bioinformatics tools."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/CE03> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE03" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Analizar e interpretar bioinformáticamente los datos que se derivan de las tecnologías ómicas, y proponer soluciones bioinformáticas en relación a dichos datos/ Analyzing and interpreting bioinformatically data derived from ?omics technologies, and proposing bioinformatics solutions according to such data."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/CE05> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE05" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Utilizar herramientas de biología computacional para el análisis genómico, incluida la genómica comparativa y biología evolutiva/ Using computational biology tools for genomics analyses, including comparative genomics and evolutionary biology."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/CE10> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE10" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Conocimiento de las técnicas de representación del conocimiento reutilizables y modelos de razonamiento en entornos centralizados y distribuidos a utilizar en la resolución de problemas que impliquen conducta inteligente/ Knowing reusable techniques for knowledge representation and reasoning models in centralized and distributed environments, and when to used them for problem solving."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/CG01> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG01" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Poseer los conocimientos que constituyen la base científica y tecnológica de la Biología computacional, lo que permitirá el desarrollo de ideas originales en este campo, en un contexto de investigación o desarrollo/ Having the scientific and technological knowledge in which Computational Biology is based, which will allow the development of original ideas in this field, in the context of both research or development."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/CG03> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG03" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes sepan aplicar los conocimientos adquiridos y su capacidad de resolución de problemas en entornos nuevos o poco conocidos dentro de contextos más amplios (o multidisciplinares) relacionados con el area de la Biología Computacional/ Provide students with the ability to apply the acquired knowledge to solve problems in new environments within ample or multidisciplinary contexts in the field of Computational Biology."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/CT08> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT08" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Tener capacidad de análisis y síntesis para interpretar datos relevantes y abordar los problemas desde diferentes perspectivas/ To have capacity for analysis and synthesis to interpret relevant data and approach to problems from different perspectives."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000035/2025-26/RA48> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA48" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Entender qué es el análisis de grandes volúmenes de datos, sus características, los métodos y las plataformas más importantes"@es .

